t46.text: How come I can get enough b12 from a few mcg in meat but if you take oral supliments they come in doses of 100 to 2000 mcg

t47.text: One way that gut flora are passed to young ruminants is by being licked by mature ruminants. Especially after they have been chewing cud.

t48.text: The idea that a beef cow in a feedlot needs B12 added to it's feed makes no sense when you understand the biology of the rumen.

t49.text: So a grain and hay diet based diet doesn't need to have bacteria on it because the rumen is already full of bacteria and other microbes.

t50.text: Nope, you have a few things wrong there. Firstly sheep and cattle are usually raise on pasture and some are grain finished. Secondly the rumen starting culture can come from many sources and once started it stays with them for life. Feedlot rations for cattle rarely have b12.

t51.text: Bacteria, fungi, yeast, protozoa which all feed on the partly chewed plant matter in a wet, warm anaerobic environment. Latter the microbe rich liquid enters the they sections of the gut and the microbes are digested.

t52.text: Some insects such as termites have symbiotic relationships with bacteria in their gut. Other insects eat rotting stuff.

t53.text: Commercial chocken feeds usually have meat meal in them.

t54.text: Chickens are omnivores. They loved to eat insects, mice, small reptiles, meat scraps, worms etc which are high in b12.

t55.text: The rumen is where the b12 in beef comes from.

t56.text: Herbivorous animals make there own b12 via gut microbes in either the foregut or hindgut. They don't need much supplementing.

t57.text: Most of the fish get b12 from the phytoplankton than have a symbiotic relationship with bacteria. They are low in the food chain and the B12 is distributed to all the other animals. Most seafood is very high in B12.

t58.text: B12 is found in soil but it enters our food chain via symbiotic relationships between bacteria and ruminants, insects and phytoplankton or detritivors. No animals actually eats soil as its main way to get b12.
